==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ra
<hw>Ra</hw> <pr>(r⟦aum⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A roe; a deer.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ra-</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Ra-
<hw>Ra-</hw>. <def>A prefix, from the Latin <xex>re</xex> and
<xex>ad</xex> combined, coming to us through the French and Italian. See
<er>Re-</er>, and <er>Ad-</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Raash</ent>⟦br⟧
